==Scottish Gaelic==

===Noun===
'''buird'''

# A [[table]] (genitive form)

===Related terms===
*[[bord]] (nominative form of 'buird')

===References===
'buird' is the genitive singular or nominative plural form of 'bord' meaning 'table'.  After the definite article it changes to 'bhuird' as in 'Beinn a Bhuird' - 'The table mountain'.

Malcolm Maclennan - A pronouncing and etymological dictionary of the Gaelic language - published jointly by Acair and Aberdeen University Press.